Advisory
 
 


 
About BMO’s Global M&A Practice
 
BMO has a powerful M&A practice that delivers world-class advisory services to our clients in North America and around the world. With nearly 100 experienced professionals, our M&A team works closely with BMO’s sector specialists and other product professionals to provide clients with our best strategic advice.
 
We can help you evaluate and, if appropriate, pursue emerging opportunities, from a value-added merger or acquisition to realigning your capital structure to maximizing shareholder value through a sale of assets, or of the company as a whole. In the U.S., we specialize in providing hands-on M&A advice to corporations, financial sponsors and family-owned companies within the mid-cap space. With the agility of an advisory boutique organization and the resources of a large, diversified and well capitalized financial institution, BMO Capital Markets can help your company reach its most ambitious goals.
 
Industry Expertise


 
Capabilities:
 

Extensive advisory experience in North American and international M&A including mergers, acquisitions, divestitures,  joint ventures, leveraged buyouts and takeover defenses
Expertise in restructuring, recapitalizations, and North American bankruptcy processes
Well-established client relationships across North American industry sectors
Strong track record in both contested bids and friendly transactions

                      Acquisition & Divestiture focusing on the Energy sector
                      
Provides buy-and-sell side advisory, fairness opinions and valuations

View A&D Advisory Publications
 
View current deals

Well-positioned real estate brokerage group

 
BMO completes acquisition of M&A advisory firm Greene Holcomb Fisher


