BMO Capital Partners






Best for
Details
Portfolio
Our team
Offices





										BMO Capital Partners



Best for
Details
Portfolio
Our team
Offices




 

 






Best for
 

Whether your business is seeking capital for acquisitions, expansion, working capital or to provide liquidity options for its shareholders, BMO Capital Partners has the investment solutions that will help you achieve your goals.

 


Companies with the following business profile:
 

Historically profitable and positive EBITDA;
Capable and highly committed management team;
Attractive market dynamics (large and growing market/fragmented industry)
Private and public companies
Demonstrated competitive advantage in respective field
No primary industries (for example mining extraction, etc.) and no start-up/early stage companies



Companies with the following investment characteristics:
 

Investment size of up to $20 million
Investments in the form of straight subordinated debt, subordinated debt with equity enhancement, convertible debentures or equity (preferred and common)
Investments are tailored to meet the needs of the specific opportunity
Investment horizon of up to seven years











Details


Subordinated Debt/Mezzanine and Equity Investments
 
Established companies can optimize their capital structure using a customized subordinated debt or equity investment solution.
 
BMO Capital Partners typically serves as a key participant within your larger financing solution. Often working alongside the senior lender, our subordinated debt and equity investments are individually structured according to the unique circumstances and needs of your business.
As a partner in your business, our team of professionals commits to give your company the time and attention required to support your needs. With our experience, expertise and judgment working on your behalf, you can be assured of receiving a financial solution designed to provide you with the flexibility and capital needed to help you achieve your goals.












Portfolio
 
Currently, our portfolio consists of over 50 investments in a variety of industries, including: 

 
 



										Business Services
								



										Health Services
								



										Manufacturing and Industrial Products
								



										Consumer Products
								




A Selection of Experience  (264 KB - PDF)










Our team
 






Alex Baniczky, 
										Vice President
								


alex.baniczky@bmo.com
 


												Alex is the head of the BMO Capital Partners and Mid-Market Mergers & Acquisitions lines of business with a focus on private equity, subordinated debt and M&A transactions across Canada. Alex brings over 20 years of experience in investment, project, and structured financing. Alex joined BMO in 1998 and has held a variety of senior level positions within the BMO financial group.
												Alex is a member of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of Ontario and has a BA (Honours) from Queens University at Kingston.
										








Evan Bennitt, 
										Managing Director Ontario
								


evan.bennitt@bmo.com
 

Evan Bennitt is a Managing Director of BMO Capital Partners and shares responsibility for overseeing investments in Ontario.  Evan has more than 15-years of middle-market leveraged finance experience and prior to joining BMOCP led CIT’s Leveraged Finance business in Canada.  Evan holds a Bachelor of Commerce from the University of Windsor, and is a CFA charter holder.








Dale Tingley, 
										Managing Director Ontario
								


dale.tingley@bmo.com
 


												Dale joined BMO Capital Partners in 2014 and shares responsibility for overseeing investments in Ontario and Atlantic Canada. He brings over fifteen years of principal investing experience, having invested across a wide variety of industries and transaction types. Dale began his career at Working Ventures Inc. followed by a move to CAI Capital Management in 2003 where he focused on North American mid-market buyouts, primarily in aerospace & defense, health care services, waste management, power generation, and business services. Most recently, Dale was Head of Investments for Aquila Infrastructure Management.

												Dale holds a B.A. in Economics and a Diploma of Engineering from the University of Prince Edward Island, an MBA from the Schulich School of Business, and the ICD.D designation.
										








Lee Grimshaw, 
										Managing Director Western Canada
								


lee.grimshaw@bmo.com
 

Lee Grimshaw is a Managing Director of BMO Capital Partners and is responsible for overseeing investments in Western Canada. Lee has extensive industry and corporate experience in Aircraft Engines, Aerospace and Appliances, in addition to 10 years of financial services industry experience in subordinated debt, equity, senior debt cash flow and asset backed transactions. Lee holds a degree in Commerce, has an MBA in Finance, and is a CFA charter holder. He is also an alumnus of the GE Financial Management Program. 











