BMO Capital Markets Reiterates “Hold” Rating for Greif Bros. Corporation (GEF)


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 26th, 2017 // No Comments




BMO Capital Markets reissued their hold rating on shares of Greif Bros. Corporation (NYSE:GEF)  in a research report report published on Sunday, July 16th. The brokerage currently has a $55.00 price objective on the industrial products company’s stock.
Several other research firms have also weighed in on GEF. KeyCorp  reaffirmed a sell rating and issued a $47.00 price objective on shares of Greif Bros. Corporation in a research note on Thursday, June 8th. Zacks Investment Research lowered Greif Bros. Corporation from a hold rating to a sell rating in a research note on Tuesday, May 2nd. BidaskClub raised Greif Bros. Corporation from a sell rating to a hold rating in a research report on Tuesday, July 11th. ValuEngine raised Greif Bros. Corporation from a hold rating to a buy rating in a research report on Friday, June 9th. Finally, Bank of America Corporation  set a $60.00 price target on Greif Bros. Corporation and gave the stock a buy rating in a research report on Saturday, June 10th. One equities research analyst  has rated the stock with a sell rating, four have assigned  a hold rating and five have assigned  a buy rating to the stock. The company currently has a consensus rating of Hold and an average price target of $56.50.


 Get Greif Bros. Corporation alerts:



Shares of Greif Bros. Corporation (NYSE:GEF) opened at 57.00 on Friday. The stock has a market capitalization of $2.73 billion, a PE ratio of 28.39 and a beta of 1.37. The stock has a 50 day moving average of $56.22 and a 200-day moving average of $56.23. Greif Bros. Corporation has a 52 week low of $38.52 and a 52 week high of $63.04. 





Greif Bros. Corporation (NYSE:GEF) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Wednesday, June 7th. The industrial products company reported $0.67 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.74 by $0.07. Greif Bros. Corporation had a return on equity of 16.17% and a net margin of 2.81%. The business had revenue of $887.40 million during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $891.22 million. During the same period in the previous year, the business posted $0.47 earnings per share. The firm’s quarterly revenue was up 5.7% on a year-over-year basis.  On average, equities research analysts expect that  Greif Bros. Corporation will post $2.89 EPS for the current year. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION WARNING: “BMO Capital Markets Reiterates “Hold” Rating for Greif Bros. Corporation (GEF)” was  reported by Chaffey Breeze and is the sole property of of Chaffey Breeze. If you are accessing this piece on another website, it was stolen and reposted in violation of U.S. and international copyright and trademark legislation. The original version of this piece can be viewed at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/26/greifs-gef-hold-rating-reiterated-at-bmo-capital-markets-updated.html. 
The company also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Saturday, July 1st. Stockholders of record on Monday, June 19th were issued a $0.42 dividend. The ex-dividend date of this dividend  was Thursday, June 15th. This represents a $1.68 dividend on an annualized basis and a dividend yield of 2.95%. Greif Bros. Corporation’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is 103.07%. 
In related news, major shareholder Shannon J. Diener acquired 5,189 shares of the stock in a transaction that occurred on Thursday, July 6th. The stock was purchased at an average cost of $62.37 per share, for a total transaction of $323,637.93. Following the purchase, the insider now directly owns 10,189 shares in the company, valued at $635,487.93. The purchase was disclosed in a legal filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is accessible through this link. 16.37% of the stock is owned by corporate insiders. 
A number of hedge funds and other institutional investors have recently modified their holdings of GEF. LS Investment Advisors LLC increased its position in shares of  Greif Bros. Corporation by 17.9% in the second quarter. LS Investment Advisors LLC now owns 2,022 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $113,000 after buying an additional 307 shares during the last quarter.  Oregon Public Employees Retirement Fund raised its position in shares of  Greif Bros. Corporation by 5.0% in the second quarter. Oregon Public Employees Retirement Fund now owns 9,323 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $520,000 after buying an additional 446 shares during the period.  Tower Research Capital LLC TRC raised its position in shares of  Greif Bros. Corporation by 106.7% in the first quarter. Tower Research Capital LLC TRC now owns 2,919 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $161,000 after buying an additional 1,507 shares during the period.  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. raised its position in shares of  Greif Bros. Corporation by 19.0% in the first quarter. Goldman Sachs Group Inc. now owns 150,861 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $8,311,000 after buying an additional 24,058 shares during the period.  Finally, Bank of Nova Scotia acquired a new position in shares of  Greif Bros. Corporation during the first quarter worth about $3,198,000. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  49.32% of the company’s stock. 
About Greif Bros. Corporation
Greif, Inc is a producer of industrial packaging products and services. The Company’s segments are Rigid Industrial Packaging & Services; Paper Packaging & Services; Flexible Products & Services, and Land Management. The Rigid Industrial Packaging & Services segment is engaged in the production and sale of rigid industrial packaging products, and services, such as container life cycle management, filling, logistics, warehousing and other packaging services.







